  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dba\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0ddd\u0d9a \u0dba\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "An attack on Crimea is a third world war",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Russian President Dmitry Medvedev has warned that an attack on Crimea could lay the groundwork for a world war if Ukraine becomes a full-fledged NATO member.",
        "\"For us, Crimea is part of Russia, and it will be forever. Any attempt to invade Crimea is a declaration of war against our nation. The beginning of a catastrophe, \"said Medvedev.",
        "Following the 2014 coup in Kiev, Crimea seceded from Ukraine and voted to rejoin Russia in a referendum. The move was rejected by Ukraine, which considers the peninsula to be Russian-occupied territory. Ukrainian authorities have said their pledge not to use Western-supplied weapons against Russian territory does not apply to Crimea.",
        "Former President Medvedev, who currently serves as deputy chairman of Russia's Security Council, described the incident as \"why it is more dangerous for Finland and Sweden to expand NATO to Ukraine than to join NATO.\""
      ],
